<h4>HTML table layout</h4>
For basic styling—light padding and only horizontal dividers—add the base class .table to any table element. 
<h5>Option classes for Table Layout</h5>
<ul>
    <li>table-hover : Hover style for table. </li>
    <li>table-bordered : Bordered table style  </li>
    <li>table-condensed : Makes tables more compact by cutting cell padding in half. </li>
</ul>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
    &lt;table class=&quot;table&quot;&gt;  &lt;-- here you are applying table class first and then applying the optional class. for eg: class="table table-bordered" will give bordered table--&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;Column 1&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;Column 2&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;Column 3&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
    &lt;tr&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;Row 2, Column 1&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt; row 2, Column 2&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;td&gt;Row 2,Column 3&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
</pre>
<table class="table table-bordered table-hover">
    <tr>
        <th>1st</th>
        <th>2nd</th>
        <th>3rd</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Column 1</td>
        <td>Column 2</td>
        <td>Column 3</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Row 2, Column 1</td>
        <td>row 2, Column 2</td>
        <td>Row 2,Column 3</td>
    </tr>
</table>




<h3>Form Styles </h3>

Default styles
Individual form controls receive styling, but without any required base class on the  form tag or large changes in markup. Results in stacked, left-aligned labels on top of form controls.

<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
&lt;form&gt;
  &lt;fieldset&gt;
    &lt;legend&gt;Legend&lt;/legend&gt;
    &lt;label&gt;Label name&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type something…&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;help-block&quot;&gt;Example block-level help text here.&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;label class=&quot;checkbox&quot;&gt;
      &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot;&gt; Check me out
    &lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;button type=&quot;submit&quot; class=&quot;btn&quot;&gt;Submit&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/fieldset&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;
</pre>
<h4>Output of the above code</h4>
<form>
    <fieldset>
        <legend>Legend</legend>
        <label>Label name</label>
        <input type="text" placeholder="Type something…">
        <span class="help-block">Example block-level help text here.</span>
        <label class="checkbox">
            <input type="checkbox">
            Check me out
        </label>
        <button type="submit" class="btn">Submit</button>
    </fieldset>
</form>


